WEBVTT

00:00.320 --> 00:03.034
Vincent, Matthew, thank you
so much for coming in

00:03.044 --> 00:05.177
- on such short notice.
- Let me stop you right there.

00:05.187 --> 00:06.804
We know why you called us in.

00:06.814 --> 00:08.929
This is a fancy-shmancy school,

00:08.940 --> 00:11.407
and tuition alone isn't gonna keep Daddy

00:11.409 --> 00:12.909
in his wood-paneled office.

00:12.911 --> 00:15.211
No, this isn't a meeting.
It's a shakedown.

00:15.213 --> 00:17.880
Yeah, well, joke's on you
'cause we don't have any money.

00:17.882 --> 00:19.415
- Nope.
- What's up?

00:19.417 --> 00:20.650
I know.

00:20.652 --> 00:22.385
Your son's on a full scholarship,

00:22.387 --> 00:24.754
and you steal toilet paper
every time you come here.

00:27.325 --> 00:28.558
Thanks.

00:28.560 --> 00:31.816
The reason I called you in is because
Michael wrote an English essay

00:31.827 --> 00:33.963
that, frankly, we all found
a little troubling.

00:33.965 --> 00:38.167
The assignment was for Michael to
describe his morning routine and...

00:38.169 --> 00:41.103
You know what? Why don't you
just read it for yourselves?

00:42.155 --> 00:44.473
<i>My morning ritual by Michael Patel.</i>

00:44.475 --> 00:46.108
<i>Each morning begins the same.</i>

00:46.110 --> 00:47.877
<i>First, I take in the headlines</i>

00:47.879 --> 00:50.012
<i>from my most trusted
news source... Snapchat.</i>

00:50.014 --> 00:52.248
<i>Second, I tweet "good morning"
at Rihanna.</i>

00:52.250 --> 00:54.951
<i>And, finally, I wait to see
what kind of woman my father,</i>

00:54.953 --> 00:56.953
<i>Vince, brought home the night before.</i>

00:56.955 --> 00:59.055
<i>I've never met so many
different kinds of women...</i>

00:59.057 --> 01:02.291
<i>bartenders, meter maids,
frozen-yogurt cashiers,</i>

01:02.293 --> 01:05.061
<i>even an antelope from "Lion King."</i>

01:09.288 --> 01:11.894
<i>Each morning is like a new
episode of "The Bachelor,"</i>

01:11.905 --> 01:14.036
<i>except Vince likes diversity.</i>

01:14.038 --> 01:17.807
Okay, so what's the problem?
I come off pretty good in that.

01:17.809 --> 01:20.242
I think what w... what we're
concerned about

01:20.244 --> 01:22.712
is one of our students
being exposed to such a display

01:22.714 --> 01:24.547
of wanton sexual excess.

01:24.549 --> 01:26.215
"Sexual excess"? No, no, no.

01:26.217 --> 01:27.550
What I have are appropriate,

01:27.552 --> 01:30.486
loving relations
between two people who are

01:30.488 --> 01:32.188
on dating apps after 11:00 p.m.

01:32.190 --> 01:35.257
Dean, I am so sorry for my brother's...

01:35.259 --> 01:37.326
what is the word... horniness.

01:37.328 --> 01:39.695
I promise, as long as
Michael's living with us,

01:39.697 --> 01:41.266
- Vince and I will not date.
- Wait.

01:41.277 --> 01:42.661
Vince, let's go.

